-- Iran Starts Military Drill to Show Nation’s Readiness, TV Says
-- B y   L a d a n e   N a s s e r i
-- 2012-07-02T04:54:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-02/iran-starts-military-drill-to-show-nation-s-readiness-tv-says.html
Iran ’s Revolutionary Guard will hold
a three-day military exercise starting today to showcase the
nation’s “resolve and readiness,” state-run Press TV reported,
citing aviation commander General Amir-Ali Hajizadeh.  In the exercise, named the Great Prophet 7, long, medium,
and short-range missiles stationed in various locations across
the country will be used against targets in Iran’s northern
Semnan desert, Hajizadeh said, the news channel reported.  Fighter jets and unmanned bombers will also be used on the
final day of the exercise, Hajizadeh said in the report,
published on Press TV’s website yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
